教學方法 Teaching Strategies
      A NIDS is an intrusion detection system that tries to detect malicious activity such as denial of service attacks, port scans or even attempts to crack into computers by monitoring network traffic. The NIDS need the two most important technologies are packet classification and packet payload inspection. In this course, we will learn and discuss these two technologies and study new methods    

